          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to handle monetary values. Its primary purpose is to return a default value of zero when a NULL monetary value is encountered. This function is useful in scenarios where monetary calculations or reports require a non-null value to avoid errors or incorrect results."
